      • duration

        public JFXAnimationTemplateConfig.Builder duration(Duration duration)
        The total Duration of this animation.
        The given Duration is the base for all JFXTemplateProcess.percent(double, double...) definitions.
        If there exist a JFXTemplateProcess.time(Duration, Duration...) definition with a greater Duration, the animation will take longer.
        Parameters:
        duration - the animation Duration.
        Returns:
        the JFXAnimationTemplateConfig.Builder instance.

      • interpolator

        public JFXAnimationTemplateConfig.Builder interpolator(Interpolator interpolator)
        The global Interpolator which is set to all JFXTemplateActions without a defined Interpolator with JFXAnimationTemplateAction.Builder.interpolator(Interpolator).
        If no Interpolator is defined, the Interpolator.LINEAR is default.
        The InterpretationMode is InterpretationMode.STATIC.
        Parameters:
        interpolator - the global Interpolator.
        Returns:
        the JFXAnimationTemplateConfig.Builder instance.

        public JFXAnimationTemplateConfig.Builder interpolator(InterpretationMode interpolatorInterpretationMode,
                                                       Supplier<Interpolator> interpolatorSupplier)
        Same as interpolator(Supplier) but with an InterpretationMode.
        If InterpretationMode.DYNAMIC is defined, the Interpolator is evaluated during animation runtime which means, that the Interpolator is exchangeable while an animation is running.
        Parameters:

        the JFXAnimationTemplateConfig.Builder instance.

      • fluentTransition

        public JFXAnimationTemplateConfig.Builder fluentTransition(Direction fluentTransitionDirection)
        Defines a FluentTransitionInterpolator for all actions without a set JFXAnimationTemplateAction.Builder.fluentTransition(Direction).
        This Interpolator uses the current value from a target WritableValue as start- or end value.
        Useful if an animation action is interpolated after an interruption which gets otherwise clipped.
        Parameters:
        fluentTransitionDirection - the Direction of the FluentTransitionInterpolator.
        Returns:
        the JFXAnimationTemplateConfig.Builder instance.

      • fromToAutoGen

        public JFXAnimationTemplateConfig.Builder fromToAutoGen(boolean fromToAutoGen)
        If true generates for every action target which has no action definition for animation start (JFXTemplateProcess.percent(double, double...) with 0 percent, JFXTemplateProcess.time(Duration, Duration...) with Duration.ZERO) or end (JFXTemplateProcess.percent(double, double...) with 100 percent, JFXTemplateProcess.time(Duration, Duration...) with max Duration), the corresponding actions.
        This emulates the corresponding behavior of a CSS animation.
        Parameters:
        fromToAutoGen - the fromToAutoGen boolean.
        Returns:
        the JFXAnimationTemplateConfig.Builder instance.

      • autoReset

        public JFXAnimationTemplateConfig.Builder autoReset(boolean autoReset)
        If true resets all action targets to the values previously set before the animation was build.
        The behaviour is similar to the CSS animation-fill-mode: backwards; definition.
        Parameters:
        autoReset - the autoReset boolean.
        Returns:
        the JFXAnimationTemplateConfig.Builder instance.
